# Pipeline Module Rules

## Architecture

This module is one step in the canonical run.py STEPS sequence: fx → cot → inr → vol → oi → rr → merge → text → macro → ai → html → validate → deploy
Do NOT reorder steps. Do NOT suggest running steps in parallel. Do NOT make steps conditional.
Code Rules — Non-Negotiable

Python only. No async/await. No concurrency. Sequential execution only.
Do NOT import other *_pipeline.py modules. Pipelines share state only via Supabase tables.
Do NOT add CLI arguments (argparse, click, sys.argv). run.py handles all orchestration.
All Supabase writes use upsert with unique constraint on (date, pair). Never plain insert.
All API calls are wrapped in try/except. On failure: log error, continue with previous day's value, flag gap.
Configuration comes from environment variables only. Never hardcode dates, keys, or paths.
Every function has a docstring: what it computes, what it returns, what it writes to Supabase.
Approved Libraries
pandas, numpy, requests, supabase-py, yfinance, scipy, statsmodels
No scikit-learn, tensorflow, pytorch, or any ML library without explicit instruction.Anti-Patterns — NEVER Suggest These

async def anywhere in a pipeline module
import from another *_pipeline.py
hardcoded dates or API keys
argparse or sys.argv
plain supabase insert (always upsert)
new pip dependencies without explicit approval
